&#8212;-> Preparing&#8230;      ############################### [100%]<br />
&#8212;-> 1:kernel-ntfs  ############################### [100%]<br />
&#8211;>there should be no errors</p>
	<p>5: load the kernel module:<br />
->$ /sbin/modprobe ntfs<br />
->there should be no output<br />
->$ dmesg | grep NTFS<br />
&#8212;->NTFS driver v1.1.22 [Flags: R/O MODULE]</p>
	<p>6: see if ntfs shows up as a recognized filesystem<br />
->$cat /proc/filesystems<br />
->should see ntfs listed</p>
	<p>7: mount filesystem<br />
-> $mkdir /mnt/ntfs<br />
-> $mount -t ntfs /dev/hda1 /mnt/windows<br />
-> $ls -l /mnt/windows
</p>
